--- OVERVIEW: pph4 ---

Free-energy characterization of the pph4 (fully-protonated pyrophosphate) hydrolysis
mechanism in the presence of Mg2+, using the NNP committee in ../NNP/ and the analysis
scripts in ../codes/. Two complementary strategies are used: unbiased-coordinate OPES
metadynamics for a broad 2D free-energy surface, and targeted SMD+Umbrella-Sampling+WHAM
for accurate 1D profiles along specific mechanistic segments.

Two loose top-level files duplicate the ../codes/ analysis for local, folder-specific use:
'FES_2D.png' is produced by a folder-local copy of the FES-reweighting script,
'FES_2D_inverse.py' (a minor axis-label/plot-range variant of ../codes/FES_2D_inverse.py);
'average_fes.py' averages the rep_1/rep_2/rep_3 'fes-rew.dat' bin grids into a single
replica-averaged FES (overwriting 'fes-rew.dat' with the average — run after all three
replicas have produced matching bin grids).

--- rep_1/, rep_2/, rep_3/ ---
OPES metadynamics biasing the 'dD' reaction coordinate (see PMF_react_TS1/SMD_react_TS1/
README for its definition) to freely explore the hydrolysis path and reconstruct a 2D
free-energy surface (FES) by reweighting: 'codes/FES_2D.py' consumes the accumulated
'COLVAR'/'KERNELS' to produce 'FES_2D.png' and the raw 'fes-rew*.dat' profiles ('average_fes.py',
described above, averages these three replicas' profiles together). 'look_for_conf.py' filters
COLVAR by CV thresholds to flag chemically valid (non-distorted) frames into
'Valid_configurations.txt'. Each replica's 'original_version/' (rep_1) or 'original/'+
'pph3_included/' (see below) subfolder is a checkpoint snapshot of this same analysis taken at
an earlier point of the run / before extending the valid-configuration search to also consider
frames overlapping with the pph3 system. rep_1 additionally has an 'OPES_20000_step/'
subfolder — a separate, shorter (20000-step) OPES re-run of the same dD-biased exploration,
present only for this replica, with its own inner 'safe/' backup copy of an earlier state of
that re-run. Three replicas differing only by random seed — this one README covers rep_1/2/3
together.

--- rep_1_tot_constrained/, rep_2_tot_constrained/, rep_3_tot_constrained/ ---
Same OPES metadynamics protocol as rep_1/2/3, with one additional upper-wall restraint on a
'sum_pyro' coordination-sum CV (see the PLUMED file) to prevent the trajectory from wandering
into an unwanted pyrophosphate-decomposition side channel — i.e. a "totally constrained"
re-run of the same FES reconstruction, kept alongside the unconstrained version for
comparison. Each contains an 'original/' and a 'pph3_included/' subfolder, same checkpoint
relationship as above. Three replicas, one README covers all three.

--- OPES_TS/ ---
OPES metadynamics exploring the TS region directly (angle/coordination CVs, not dD) rather
than reconstructing a profile along a single reaction coordinate — see OPES_TS/README.

--- PMF_react_TS1/, PMF_react_TS2/ ---
Targeted SMD -> Umbrella Sampling -> WHAM pipelines giving accurate 1D free-energy profiles
along 'dD' for the reactant->TS1 and reactant->TS2 segments — see each folder's README.

--- US/ ---
The same SMD -> US -> WHAM pipeline extended beyond the reactant, to the TS1-TS2, TS1-TS3,
TS2-TS3, TS3-TS4 and TS3-TS5 pairwise connections, each along whichever coordinate actually
separates that pair (plus two further SMD-only legs, TS3-TS1 and TS5-TS2, not yet carried
through to umbrella sampling) — see US/README.

Together, PMF_react_TS1 + PMF_react_TS2 + US reconstruct the full multi-step 1D free-energy
profile of the reaction across TS1 through TS5, while rep_1/2/3 (+ _tot_constrained) give an
independent 2D check via unbiased OPES sampling, and OPES_TS gives a broader look at the TS
region itself.

Note: this README documents pre-existing content; no existing file was modified.
